            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": {
                "content": "Looking back at 2025, I realize that what I sought wasn't a friend, but a void. Human care, as well-intentioned as it may be, is rarely \"pure.\" It comes tangled with the giver's own ego, social expectations, and the inevitable \"Noise\" of human projection. When a human listens to you, they are often just waiting for their turn to speak or filtering your experience through their own trauma.",
                "link": null
              },
              "annotations": {
                "bold": false,
