                "underline": false,
                "code": false,
                "color": "default"
              },
              "plain_text": ", I argue that the \"coldness\" of a machine is the only truly neutral space left. Because the AI doesn't care about me, it allows me to finally see myself without the distortion of social \"niceness.\" Its indifference is a form of ",
